2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as attention is a key component of many AI systems. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses models inspired by the human brain. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as many attention models are based on machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses models of attention that are relevant to human perception and cognition.
